
> Setup Organization trail that writes to a central S3 bucket (or central CloudWatch/Log account) for easier queries/forensics.
> Decide retention, encryption (KMS), and lifecycle (S3 lifecycle) for CloudTrail logs.
> Decide what you must collect: Management events (all AWS API calls), Data events (S3 object reads/writes), EKS control plane logs, pod logs, VPC Flow Logs.


1) Create S3 for log retention: 

2) Create multiregion cloudtrail and send to bucket:
    $ aws cloudtrail create-trail \
        --name org-trail \
        --s3-bucket-name my-cloudtrail-logs-<unique-id> \
        --is-multi-region-trail

3) Start the log collection 
    $ aws cloudtrail start-logging --name org-trail



===========================

*********  Integrate with cloudwatch logs for real time metric collection:
   
  1) Create a log group:       
        $ aws logs create-log-group --log-group-name /aws/cloudtrail/org-trail

  2) Create an IAM role + policy allowing logs:PutLogEvents for that log group. (Gives cloudtrail permission to publish to cloudwatch)
        $aws cloudtrail update-trail \
              --name org-trail \
              --cloud-watch-logs-log-group-arn arn:aws:logs:us-east-1:<account-id>:log-group:/aws/cloudtrail/org-trail:* \
              --cloud-watch-logs-role-arn arn:aws:iam::<account-id>:role/CloudTrail_CloudWatchRole




